    {
      "id": "57dd3036_f589ded8",
      "file_path": "participant/participant-impl/participant-impl-simulator/src/main/resources/config/CDSParticipantConfig.json",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 28,
      "message": "Yeah - thinking about this more. I know the other repos have these also most likely in src/main/resources. We can do the same as them. But are they needed? Possibly for a development environment - but then again if its configurable all you have to do is be able to set an environment variable or command line to point to a test file. The thing is, the user/password just happens to be the same that we use in OOM by default. I understand that can be changed but we really should have been more careful.\n\nOthers?",
