    {
      "id": "1abd95d1_af50aa76",
      "file_path": "participant/participant-impl/participant-impl-simulator/src/main/resources/config/CDSParticipantConfig.json",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 28,
      "message": "I can modify the CSITs to use message-router, instead.  However, they would still need to mount their own config files, as we use https in the CSITs, while we've chosen to use plain http in the config files that come with the repos.  (In addition, the PAP repo includes policy-distribution in the health check, but I didn't want the PAP CSIT to depend on distribution, so it requires a config override anyway.)\n\nBTW: OOM should enable https, too.  If it doesn't, that's a bug.  If we were OK changing the repos to use https, instead, then we could remove most of the overrides in the CSITs.  (You can always use the gen_keystore.sh script in the CSITs to generate a certificate for use in other environments.)\n\nFor now, I think the latest file (i.e., containing \"message-router\") is good, but wouldn't mind continuing this discussion.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-11 17:06:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5998a141_8823583a",
      "unresolved": false
    },
